description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surgical Directorate &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancy - Band 8a Critical Care Matron&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours of work - 37.5 hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A great opportunity has arisen due to our current long standing critical care matron retiring. We are looking for a highly motivated, energetic, experienced and enthusiastic Critical Care senior nurse to lead our Critical Care Unit at Ysbyty Glan Clwyd on a permanent basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Surgical Directorate is looking for a forward thinking, innovative senior matron to join our matron and operational management team. If you are committed to giving high standards of care, have a strong focus on patient safety, can work flexibly to lead your team and have experience in Critical care and leading a team we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Critical Care Unit is committed to delivering high quality, evidence-based care, which focuses on the individual needs of the patients and their relatives. We pride ourselves on the privilege of serving our local population and delivering high quality care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidate will be provided with a personal training plan and mentorship with the Directorate Head of Nursing. The successful candidate will be required to undertake site support for Matron of the Day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply you will need to demonstrate significant experience as a senior nurse leader at Band 7 or above. The role requires you to be an excellent communicator, leader and passionate about critical care nursing. Your portfolio must demonstrate that of a high profile clinical leader and have had regular management experience of a clinical area; with critical care experience is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want the opportunity to lead our amazing dedicated team that provide safe and compassionate care to our critically ill patients, have an innovative and dynamic approach to developing services and our staff then we would welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 12/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Janet Garnett&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Head of nursing - Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Janet.Garnett@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01745 583910 extension 3884&lt;/p&gt;
